Executive Profile
Mark B. Grier  Executive Vice President of Financial Management, The Prudential Insurance Company of America, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. Mark B. Grier is an Executive Vice President of Financial Management at The Prudential Insurance Company of America, Inc. Mr. Grier serves as Director of Financial Management at Prudential Financial Inc. Prior to joining Prudential, Mr. Grier served as an Executive Vice President of Chase Manhattan Corporation from 1991 to May 1995. He served as an Executive Vice President of Prudential Financial Inc. from December 2000 to August 2002; Vice President from January ... 2000 to December 2000; Chief Financial Officer of Prudential Insurance since May 1995. He served as Executive Vice President of Corporate Governance, Executive Vice President of Financial Management at Prudential Financial, Inc. Mr. Grier served as Vice Chairman of Financial Management & International Division for Prudential Financial Inc. since August 2002. Mr. Grier has been Chairman of Global Impact Investing Network since February 15, 2017. He serves as Chairman of Achieve, Inc. and served as its Vice Chairman. He has been a Vice Chairman of Prudential Financial, Inc., since August 2002 and previously from May 1995 to June 1997. He has been Vice Chairman of The Prudential Insurance Company of America since 2002. He serves as Member of the Board of Managers of Wachovia Securities Financial Holdings, LLC. He serves as Director at The Prudential Insurance Company of America, Inc. at Prudential Variable Contract Real Property Account. He serves as Director, Member of Committee on Management and Director of Rochester Gas & Electric Corporation of RGS Energy Group, Inc. since August 2, 1999 and Rochester Gas and Electric Corp. since 1997. He has been a Director of Tragedy Assistance Program For Survivors (taps) since January 2013; Achieve, Inc., since 2009 and Prudential Financial Inc. since January 1, 2008. He served as a Director at Prudential Financial from December 1999 to January 2001. Mr. Grier served as Director of Annuity and Life Re (Holdings), Ltd. since 1998. He attended Eastern Illinois University where he received a B.A. and an M.A. in economics. He also earned an M.B.A. in finance and corporate accounting from The University of Rochester.Read Full Background




